cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS, cs.RO 

The paper focuses on using neural networks and reinforcement learning to solve combinatorial optimization problems, specifically the traveling salesman problem and the knapsack problem. This falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and robotics (cs.RO). However, given the emphasis on neural networks and reinforcement learning, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely categories.
